42
43struct diffarg {
44#ifdef __FreeBSD__
45 kthread_t *da_td;
46 struct file *da_fp; /* file to which we are reporting */
47#else
48 struct vnode *da_vp; /* file to which we are reporting */
49#endif
50 offset_t *da_offp;
51 int da_err; /* error that stopped diff search */
52 dmu_diff_record_t da_ddr;
53};
54
55#ifdef __FreeBSD__
56static int
57write_bytes(struct diffarg *da)
58{
59 struct uio auio;
60 struct iovec aiov;
61
62 aiov.iov_base = (caddr_t)&da->da_ddr;
63 aiov.iov_len = sizeof (da->da_ddr);
64 auio.uio_iov = &aiov;
65 auio.uio_iovcnt = 1;
66 auio.uio_resid = aiov.iov_len;
67 auio.uio_rw = UIO_WRITE;
68 auio.uio_offset = (off_t)-1;
69 auio.uio_segflg = UIO_SYSSPACE;
70 auio.uio_td = da->da_td;
71#ifdef _KERNEL
72 if (da->da_fp->f_type == DTYPE_VNODE)
73 bwillwrite();
74 return (fo_write(da->da_fp, &auio, da->da_td->td_ucred, 0, da->da_td));
75#else
76 fprintf(stderr, "%s: returning EOPNOTSUPP\n", __func__);
77 return (EOPNOTSUPP);
78#endif
79}
80#endif /* __FreeBSD__ */
81
82static int
83write_record(struct diffarg *da)
84{
85 ssize_t resid; /* have to get resid to get detailed errno */
86
87 if (da->da_ddr.ddr_type == DDR_NONE) {
88 da->da_err = 0;
89 return (0);
90 }
91
92#ifdef __FreeBSD__
93 da->da_err = write_bytes(da);
94#else
95 da->da_err = vn_rdwr(UIO_WRITE, da->da_vp, (caddr_t)&da->da_ddr,
96 sizeof (da->da_ddr), 0, UIO_SYSSPACE, FAPPEND,
97 RLIM64_INFINITY, CRED(), &resid);
98#endif
99 *da->da_offp += sizeof (da->da_ddr);
100 return (da->da_err);
101}
102
103static int
104report_free_dnode_range(struct diffarg *da, uint64_t first, uint64_t last)
105{
106 ASSERT(first <= last);
107 if (da->da_ddr.ddr_type != DDR_FREE ||
108 first != da->da_ddr.ddr_last + 1) {
109 if (write_record(da) != 0)
110 return (da->da_err);
111 da->da_ddr.ddr_type = DDR_FREE;
112 da->da_ddr.ddr_first = first;
113 da->da_ddr.ddr_last = last;
114 return (0);
115 }
116 da->da_ddr.ddr_last = last;
117 return (0);
118}
119
120static int
121report_dnode(struct diffarg *da, uint64_t object, dnode_phys_t *dnp)
122{
123 ASSERT(dnp != NULL);
124 if (dnp->dn_type == DMU_OT_NONE)
125 return (report_free_dnode_range(da, object, object));
126
127 if (da->da_ddr.ddr_type != DDR_INUSE ||
128 object != da->da_ddr.ddr_last + 1) {
129 if (write_record(da) != 0)
130 return (da->da_err);
131 da->da_ddr.ddr_type = DDR_INUSE;
132 da->da_ddr.ddr_first = da->da_ddr.ddr_last = object;
133 return (0);
134 }
135 da->da_ddr.ddr_last = object;
136 return (0);
137}
138
139#define DBP_SPAN(dnp, level) \
140 (((uint64_t)dnp->dn_datablkszsec) << (SPA_MINBLOCKSHIFT + \
141 (level) * (dnp->dn_indblkshift - SPA_BLKPTRSHIFT)))
142
143/* ARGSUSED */
144static int
145diff_cb(spa_t *spa, zilog_t *zilog, const blkptr_t *bp,
146 const zbookmark_phys_t *zb, const dnode_phys_t *dnp, void *arg)
147{
148 struct diffarg *da = arg;
149 int err = 0;
150
151 if (issig(JUSTLOOKING) && issig(FORREAL))
152 return (SET_ERROR(EINTR));
153
154 if (bp == NULL || zb->zb_object != DMU_META_DNODE_OBJECT)
155 return (0);
156
157 if (BP_IS_HOLE(bp)) {
158 uint64_t span = DBP_SPAN(dnp, zb->zb_level);
159 uint64_t dnobj = (zb->zb_blkid * span) >> DNODE_SHIFT;
160
161 err = report_free_dnode_range(da, dnobj,
162 dnobj + (span >> DNODE_SHIFT) - 1);
163 if (err)
164 return (err);
165 } else if (zb->zb_level == 0) {
166 dnode_phys_t *blk;
167 arc_buf_t *abuf;
168 arc_flags_t aflags = ARC_FLAG_WAIT;
169 int blksz = BP_GET_LSIZE(bp);
170 int i;
171
172 if (arc_read(NULL, spa, bp, arc_getbuf_func, &abuf,
173 ZIO_PRIORITY_ASYNC_READ, ZIO_FLAG_CANFAIL,
174 &aflags, zb) != 0)
175 return (SET_ERROR(EIO));
176
177 blk = abuf->b_data;
178 for (i = 0; i < blksz >> DNODE_SHIFT; i++) {
179 uint64_t dnobj = (zb->zb_blkid <<
180 (DNODE_BLOCK_SHIFT - DNODE_SHIFT)) + i;
181 err = report_dnode(da, dnobj, blk+i);
182 if (err)
183 break;
184 }
185 arc_buf_destroy(abuf, &abuf);
186 if (err)
187 return (err);
188 /* Don't care about the data blocks */
189 return (TRAVERSE_VISIT_NO_CHILDREN);
190 }
191 return (0);
192}
193
194int
195dmu_diff(const char *tosnap_name, const char *fromsnap_name,
196#ifdef __FreeBSD__
197 struct file *fp, offset_t *offp)
198#else
199 struct vnode *vp, offset_t *offp)
200#endif
201{
202 struct diffarg da;
203 dsl_dataset_t *fromsnap;
204 dsl_dataset_t *tosnap;
205 dsl_pool_t *dp;
206 int error;
207 uint64_t fromtxg;
208
209 if (strchr(tosnap_name, '@') == NULL ||
210 strchr(fromsnap_name, '@') == NULL)
211 return (SET_ERROR(EINVAL));
212
213 error = dsl_pool_hold(tosnap_name, FTAG, &dp);
214 if (error != 0)
215 return (error);
216
217 error = dsl_dataset_hold(dp, tosnap_name, FTAG, &tosnap);
218 if (error != 0) {
219 dsl_pool_rele(dp, FTAG);
220 return (error);
221 }
222
223 error = dsl_dataset_hold(dp, fromsnap_name, FTAG, &fromsnap);
224 if (error != 0) {
225 dsl_dataset_rele(tosnap, FTAG);
226 dsl_pool_rele(dp, FTAG);
227 return (error);
228 }
229
230 if (!dsl_dataset_is_before(tosnap, fromsnap, 0)) {
231 dsl_dataset_rele(fromsnap, FTAG);
232 dsl_dataset_rele(tosnap, FTAG);
233 dsl_pool_rele(dp, FTAG);
234 return (SET_ERROR(EXDEV));
235 }
236
237 fromtxg = dsl_dataset_phys(fromsnap)->ds_creation_txg;
238 dsl_dataset_rele(fromsnap, FTAG);
239
240 dsl_dataset_long_hold(tosnap, FTAG);
241 dsl_pool_rele(dp, FTAG);
242
243#ifdef __FreeBSD__
244 da.da_td = curthread;
245 da.da_fp = fp;
246#else
247 da.da_vp = vp;
248#endif
249 da.da_offp = offp;
250 da.da_ddr.ddr_type = DDR_NONE;
251 da.da_ddr.ddr_first = da.da_ddr.ddr_last = 0;
252 da.da_err = 0;
253
254 error = traverse_dataset(tosnap, fromtxg,
255 TRAVERSE_PRE | TRAVERSE_PREFETCH_METADATA, diff_cb, &da);
256
257 if (error != 0) {
258 da.da_err = error;
259 } else {
260 /* we set the da.da_err we return as side-effect */
261 (void) write_record(&da);
262 }
263
264 dsl_dataset_long_rele(tosnap, FTAG);
265 dsl_dataset_rele(tosnap, FTAG);
266
267 return (da.da_err);
268}
